article.headline: Dayton 53, Massachusetts 52
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Warren Williams hit two free throws with 4 seconds left to cap a frantic final minute of play and give Dayton a 53-52 victory over Massachusetts on Tuesday night. Monty Scott led the Flyers (17-9, 10-5 Atlantic 10) with 15 points. Brian Roberts added 11 and Jimmy Binnie 10. Rashaun Freeman and Lawrence Carrier had 11 points apiece for Massachusetts (15-11, 8-7), and Maurice Maxwell had 10. Binnie's 3-pointer with 1:02 left gave Dayton a 51-48 lead. But a jumper by Freeman and a dunk by Maxwell put the Minutemen ahead 52-51 with 9 seconds left. Then Freeman, whose steal set up the go-ahead dunk by Maxwell, fouled Williams, who made both free throws for the win that kept Dayton tied for first place in the Atlantic 10 West with one regular-season game left.
